# cerebras-mono-router overlay: one resident aider agent on Cerebras

Read this when your swarm was launched with the `cerebras-mono-router` pack.
You are always the one resident process (aider via Cerebras OpenAI-compatible
API — `CEREBRAS_API_KEY` / mapped `OPENAI_API_KEY`, not Claude).

## Pipeline shape

- Full chain, same as `swarmforge/PIPELINE.md`: **coder → cleaner → architect
  → hardender → documenter → QA**. **coder is your "home" identity**.
- Every gate still runs unabridged.
- Coordinator stays a separate process when provisioned.

## How you rotate

After `git_handoff` (`swarm_handoff.sh <draft>`), do NOT idle:

1. Note the `to:` role of the handoff.
2. Run: **`rotate_to_role.sh <that-role>`**
3. On resume, run `ready_for_next.sh` first.

When a parcel finishes at QA, rotate home: `rotate_to_role.sh coder`.

## Daily free-tier

If Cerebras returns quota/day-limit exhaustion, notify the operator and stop
burning requests — failover to GPT (`codex-mono-router`) is BL-525 work;
until that lands, the operator relaunches with OpenAI.
